n=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104iuy1665702557684.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iuy1665702557684.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iuy1665702557684.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"iuy1665702557684\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Disable the validation of the contents of a field against the values in the ValRep list.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__topic_d142190e1_d142191e1_d142192e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__p_d142193e1_d142194e1_d142195e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NO_VALREP_CHECK</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__section_nhm_dcv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d988568e58\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__table_d17042e1_d17043e1_d17044e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Any application assignment file </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__section_pgp_hcv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d988568e104\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__p_d142202e1_d142203e1_d142204e1\">When leaving an occurrence or during the ^STORE and\n            ^ACCEPT operations, the contents of the field are validated against the values in the\n            ValRep list. If the value does not match a value in the ValRep list, the field contents\n            are not accepted. This check generates message:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__pre_i5x_hcv_jwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">0119 (\"Error on field &lt;FIELD_NAME&gt;; Illegal ValRep value\")</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__p_d142205e1_d142206e1_d142207e1\">If the ValRep list is larger than 32768 items,\n            error 0119 may be generated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__p_d142208e1_d142209e1_d142210e1\">If no ValRep is available for the field, no check\n            is done.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iuy1665702557684__p_d142211e1_d142212e1_d142213e1\">In Uniface 6, this check was not performed, so the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NO_VALREP_CHECK</span> setting restores this behavior.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$NO_VALREP_CHECK Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Disable the validation of the contents of a field against the values in the ValRep list. $NO_VALREP_CHECK Defaults Assignment file: Any application assignment file Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description When leaving an occurrence or during the ^STORE and ^ACCEPT operations, the contents of the field are validated against the values in the ValRep list. If the value does not match a value in the ValRep list, the field contents are not accepted. This check generates message: 0119 (\"Error on field <FIELD_NAME>; Illegal ValRep value\") Copy If the ValRep list is larger than 32768 items, error 0119 may be generated. If no ValRep is available for the field, no check is done. In Uniface 6, this check was not performed, so the $NO_VALREP_CHECK setting restores this behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}